    java.lang.Comparable<Building>

    public class Building
extends EndPoint
implements java.lang.Comparable<Building>
    Building is a labeled EndPoint that marks the location of a building. It has two labels: a short name, and a long name.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Building other)
        Compares this Building to another Building. Uses lexicographical comparison of the two buildings' short names to determine relative ordering.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Building>
        Parameters:
        other - : building to be compared to
        Returns:
        the value 0 if the other building's short name is lexicographically equal to this building's short name, a value greater than 0 if this building's short name is lexicographically greater than the other building's short name, and and a value less than 0 if this building's short name is lexicographically less than the other building's short name
